; 580 BC: Thales

* Everything is water in one form or another - the world is comprised of different states of water-matter.
* The Earth is a sphere that floats on water, just as wooden ships are buoyant enough to carry heavy cargo.
* All we know from Thales is through fragmented hearsay. Whether he was an elite primitive scientist, a monadic elementalist, or a mythological memetic landmark, he offers us crucial seed-theses to grow [[The Great Human Conversation]].